-- Flaherty Says Canada Provinces Agree to Create Pooled Pension Plan System
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2010-12-20T21:16:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/flaherty-says-canada-provinces-agree-to-create-pooled-pension-plan-system.html
Canadian Finance Minister Jim
Flaherty said he has an agreement with his provincial
counterparts to create “pooled pensions.”  Flaherty, who said the plans will make it easier for small
companies and the self-employed to participate in registered
pension plans, made the announcement in Kananaskis, Alberta.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theophilos Argitis in Kananaskis, Alberta at 
 targitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
